§ 9 UPDATE-CHANNELS (stable IDs · matches cssl-hotfix::Channel)

  ┌─────┬───────────────────┬──────────┬─────────────────────────┬─────────────┐
  │ ID  │ name              │ cap-key  │ apply-boundary          │ default-on? │
  ├─────┼───────────────────┼──────────┼─────────────────────────┼─────────────┤
  │  1  │ loa.binary        │ cap-A    │ RestartRequired         │ ✗ off       │
  │  2  │ cssl.bundle       │ cap-B    │ NextFrameBoundary       │ ✗ off       │
  │  3  │ kan.weights       │ cap-C    │ AtomicHotSwap           │ ✗ off       │
  │  4  │ balance.config    │ cap-C    │ SceneTransition         │ ✗ off       │
  │  5  │ recipe.book       │ cap-E    │ SceneTransition         │ ✗ off       │
  │  6  │ nemesis.bestiary  │ cap-E    │ SceneTransition         │ ✗ off       │
  │  7  │ security.patch    │ cap-D    │ Immediate               │ ✓ ON        │
  │  8  │ storylet.content  │ cap-E    │ SceneTransition         │ ✗ off       │
  │  9  │ render.pipeline   │ cap-E    │ SceneTransition         │ ✗ off       │
  └─────┴───────────────────┴──────────┴─────────────────────────┴─────────────┘

§ BUNDLE BINARY LAYOUT  [80-byte header · then payload · then 64-byte sig]

  offset  size  field            notes
  ──────  ────  ───────────────  ──────────────────────────────────────────
  0       4     magic            "CSFX" = 0x43 0x53 0x46 0x58
  4       2     format_version   u16 LE · current = 1 · BREAKING bumps this
  6       1     channel          u8 · Channel discriminant 1..=9
  7       1     cap_role         u8 · CapRole discriminant 1..=5
  8       2     ver_major        u16 LE · semver
  10      2     ver_minor        u16 LE
  12      2     ver_patch        u16 LE
  14      2     reserved_a       u16 LE · MUST be 0
  16      8     timestamp_ns     u64 LE · build wall-clock
  24      8     payload_size     u64 LE
  32      32    payload_blake3   raw BLAKE3-256 of payload bytes
  64      16    reserved_b       16 bytes · MUST be all-zero
  ──────  ────  ───────────────  ──────────────────────────────────────────
  80      N     payload          payload_size bytes
  80+N    64    ed25519_sig      Ed25519 signature over header || payload

  Total file size = 80 + payload_size + 64.

§ APPLY-FLOW  [atomic · numbered]

  1. client receives manifest from /api/hotfix/manifest
  2. verify_manifest : Ed25519 sig against compiled-in cap-keys
  3. for each Channel where SigmaPolicy.allows_download :
       a. read installed-version meta from <dir>/<channel>/current.meta
       b. if revoked-list contains (channel, installed-version) → schedule rollback
       c. if manifest's current_version > installed → schedule update
  4. for each scheduled update :
       a. fetch bundle bytes from /api/hotfix/download or mycelium peer
       b. parse + verify_bundle (header + signature + cap-role-matches-channel)
       c. if consent ≡ PromptBeforeApply → emit PromptPending event
       d. else → apply_bundle :
            i.   write payload to <dir>/<channel>/.staged.payload
            ii.  write meta to    <dir>/<channel>/.staged.meta
            iii. if current exists, snapshot to .history/<channel>/<old>.payload
            iv.  rename .staged.payload → current     (atomic)
            v.   rename .staged.meta    → current.meta
            vi.  prune .history to N-1 + N-2
       e. emit Applied event ; store snapshot for future rollback
  5. emit cumulative PollReport

§ ROLLBACK-FLOW  [atomic · numbered]

  1. read .snapshots/<channel>.json → AppliedSnapshot
  2. read prior-payload-path from snapshot
  3. rename current → .history/<channel>/<failed>.failed.payload (forensics)
  4. rename current.meta → .history/<channel>/<failed>.failed.meta
  5. rename .history/<channel>/<prior>.payload → current
  6. rewrite current.meta with prior version + restored blake3
  7. emit RolledBack telemetry event

§ Σ-MASK CONSENT MATRIX  [per-channel · default · override-anytime]

  channel              default     override-options
  ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  loa.binary           Off         AutoApply / Prompt / Pinned
  cssl.bundle          Off         AutoApply / Prompt / Pinned
  kan.weights          Off         AutoApply / Prompt / Pinned
  balance.config       Off         AutoApply / Prompt / Pinned
  recipe.book          Off         AutoApply / Prompt / Pinned
  nemesis.bestiary     Off         AutoApply / Prompt / Pinned
  security.patch       AutoApply   Prompt / Pinned (NEVER coercive-on)
  storylet.content     Off         AutoApply / Prompt / Pinned
  render.pipeline      Off         AutoApply / Prompt / Pinned

§ TELEMETRY EVENTS  [emitted by HotfixClient · sink-side honours opt-in]

  Checked       — manifest fetched + verified
  Downloaded    — bundle bytes fetched + verified
  Applied       — apply succeeded
  RolledBack    — apply failed → reverted (or revoked-list match)
  Skipped       — Σ-mask deny / pinned / already-current
  Revoked       — locally-installed version was on revocation list
  ApplyFailed   — apply failed with reason ; sink may forward to /api/hotfix/status

§ MYCELIUM-FEDERATION  (peer-to-peer byte CDN · ¬ trust-other-peer)

  apocky.com remains the manifest-of-truth.
  Mycelium peers serve bundle BYTES once verified by the verifier-of-record.
  Verifier checks cap-key-on-file even when bytes came from a peer ; therefore
  a malicious peer cannot mutate the apply outcome. Mycelium reduces apocky.com
  bandwidth, latency, and provides offline-tolerance — but is NOT the source of
  truth for which version IS the canonical-current.

§ NON-GOALS / GUARDRAILS

  ✗ silent binary push (default-deny stops this · cap-D security-patch is the
    SOLE always-on channel and Apocky personally signs every cap-D bundle)
  ✗ telemetry of which user is on which version (only aggregate counters
    unless user explicitly opts in via Σ-mask consent for fleet-monitor)
  ✗ DRM / anti-cheat / rootkit (banned · cosmetic-only-axiom)
  ✗ pay-for-power update (any update changing balance.config requires
    cap-C signature + Apocky's public-record release-note acknowledging
    the change ; community-veto via spec/13 anti-pay-for-power axiom)

§ ATTESTATION
  ¬ harm · sovereign-revocable · Σ-mask-default-deny · rollback-atomic
  ¬ DRM · ¬ rootkit · cap-key-restricted · cosmetic-only-axiom-holds
  No hurt nor harm in the making of this, to anyone, anything, or anybody.
